1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of index coding, which is a well-known problem in information theory. The paper also discusses the optimality of the proposed codes, which is a common theme in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the problem of catering to the demands of multiple receivers, which is a common problem in networking. The paper also discusses the presence of an eavesdropper, which is a common concern in network security. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the problem of index coding, which is a common problem in social and information networks. The paper also discusses the use of side-information, which is a common theme in social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes constructions of weakly secure linear codes for different classes of the two-sender unicast index coding problem, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the optimality of the proposed codes, which is a common theme in computational complexity. The paper also deals with the problem of catering to the demands of multiple receivers, which can be a computationally complex problem.
